reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I have tried cushions like this before but their relief was only temporary. This one is different, it is more robust than the others I have tried and it is better at both supporting my spine and keeping cool during long hours of use. If you haven't gotten a lot of relief from similar products I would say this one is worth a shot!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Useful for comfortable drives
reviews.reviewText: I've lost some weight, and it's starting to make sitting a little more painful on my tailbone. Long drives were getting hard, so I got this cushion to help. It helps a ton, but I do wish it were a little more structured! It's less supportive than it was when I first got it. Also, the memory foam gets ROCK HARD when it's really cold outside, so be aware of that. (I'm not judging this cushion based on that; that's just a memory foam thing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wonderful Desk Chair Cushion
reviews.reviewText: I am so happy with this desk chair cushion! I have had it for a month now and it has remained in the same shape and has not compressed at all. Before I got the chair cushion, I was having difficulty sitting at the desk for extended periods of time due to right hip joint pain cause by a minor accident. Now I can sit for about an hour or more and there is no pain! My wife also sits at the desk on the chair cushion for periods of time when I'm not home. This really speaks to the quality of the cushion. Also, we like that the cushion has a cover with a zipper so it can be removed and washed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's very comfortable after sitting down, my job requires me to sit in front of the computer for a long time, it makes me more relaxed and reduces my pain, I think it's worth the money

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Works okay but has a very strong smell
reviews.reviewText: When I first opened this item, I was hit with an extremely strong chemical smell, almost like paint. It started to give me a headache within a few minutes so I put it outside on my balcony for a few days in hopes that the smell would dissipate. This helped some, but after using it for a full day of work, my clothes started to smell like it! I would go into a completely different room and still smell it on me.The cushion does help with neck and back pain from extended sitting and working, but I was disappointed with the smell. It appears to be an issue with the cushion and not the cover, so it's not an easy fix to wash. I would recommend the manufacturer finds a way to let their product sit and offgass before sealing and sending to the consumer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very soft and good support
reviews.reviewText: Good support especially in my office as I work sitting down 9 hours a day and have Sciatica. Very soft and doesn't slip around on my chair. Also easy to put in my desk to hide so it doesn't walk off overnight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good comfort - covers the area well
reviews.reviewText: I had to include the first photo because this is the way it showed up. Rather funny in the vacuum packed state.'Setting it free' from the vacuum it came to the full size in short order and has been comfortable to sit upon. I battle sciatica and piriformis syndrome and this has been helpful.They says it's portable - which is true, but not sure how you'd ever get it back into the compressed size save a vacuum sealer. The name is boldly embroidered on the front: UEUHFKTS. No idea what that means but I'm sure someone can come up with a funny sentence that covers it all. If so - post it please. We all gotta laugh more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very Strong Initial Smell But Incredibly Comfortable
reviews.reviewText: I have a shop where I do occasional artist markets and vendor events, and sitting for 6 to 8 hours on questionable seating arrangements was killing my back. This cushion really helped preserve my back and improved my overall experience at the events. I will say when this arrived it had a very strong smell and I had to keep it outside for a few days until it dissipated. I love how soft the material is, and how thick and squishy the cushion itself is with the memory foam material. Definitely recommend if you need to sit for extended periods of time.
